    <character-template name="Landless Knight" points="12">
        <description>
            <background>
                <para>
                    There are plenty of noble sons who are unlikely to
                    inherit anything capable of supporting them, either
                    through general poverty, or simply because they are
                    the fifth or sixth son. Such nobles face a choice of
                    going into the church, or becoming a wandering knight,
                    looking for employment, fame and fortune.
                </para>
                
                <para>
                    Such knights do not see themselves as mercenaries,
                    though the road they take is very similar to that
                    profession. They believe they fight for ideals,
                    though cash in hand, a warm meal and a roof over
                    their head will do in a pinch.
                </para>
            </background>
        </description>

